name: Create Epic Form
description: Create an epic
title: "[ðŸ’¥ Epic]: "
labels: ["scrum: epic", "triage"]
assignees:
  - jstiefel
body:
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        An epic is a large body of work that can be broken down into a number of smaller stories. It can encompass multiple teams, projects and boards.
        It usually takes 3 months to implement. Epics are most likely not only related to software.
  - type: textarea
    id: outcome
    attributes:
      label: What is the body of work?
      description: Epics describe the context for the user stories. 
      placeholder: What is the top-tier of the work hierarchy?
      value: "March 2050 Rocket Launch"
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: textarea
    id: stories
    attributes:
      label: Story Breakdown
      description: Necessary stories to implement the epic once they're created
      value: |
        Story Link 1
        Story Link 2
      placeholder: Link task issues!
    validations:
      required: false
